						               													<description>You are a Venetian jeweler. Make a bracelet with Venetian glass beads known as &amp;ldquo;rondelles.&amp;rdquo;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In Rondel Rummy, players compete to make bracelets. Players begin each round by adding beads to either side of their empty metal hoop. Once everyone has a full bracelet, players take turns exchanging with the beads on a metal tray.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In order for a bracelet to be complete, the beads must create a rainbow with every available color or a symmetrical design. When the hoops are closed, players can strategically rotate their beads. After a player completes their bracelet, the other players may each make one more exchange. Points are scored based on the number of colors on a complete bracelet. Rounds are repeated until a player or players score 5 points, winning the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The components are tactile and interactive. Bright beads and metal hoops make up the bracelets. Beads are held in a soft bag and displayed on a metal tray. Players keep track of their points using colorful finger rings. The components and engaging rules make for a unique experience.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
